The serif [Gentium font](http://scripts.sil.org/Gentium) and the sans [DejaVu font](http://dejavu.sourceforge.net/) is included on every Webconverger distribution since version 2.21.


# Installing the default Webconverger fonts on a Debian/Ubuntu machine:

  1. `monty:~% sudo apt-get install ttf-gentium ttf-dejavu`
  2. Restart your browser

# On other operating systems:


 * [Gentium download](http://scripts.sil.org/Gentium_download)
 * [DejaVu download](http://dejavu.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Download)

# Microsoft fonts

The package _msttcorefonts_ contains the Microsoft fonts like Arial, Verdana etc. Since there are license and freedom issues shipping these proprietary fonts with Webconverger, they have been dropped.